          <h5 class="card-title">Female Reproductive Anatomy</h5>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <p>
              Understanding your reproductive anatomy is essential for
              maintaining good sexual and reproductive health.
            </p>

            <h6 class="mt-4">External Anatomy</h6>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Vulva</strong> - The external genital organs, including:
              </li>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Labia majora</strong> - Outer folds of skin that
                  protect the genital area
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Labia minora</strong> - Inner folds of skin with many
                  nerve endings
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Clitoris</strong> - Highly sensitive organ with
                  thousands of nerve endings focused on sexual pleasure
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Urethral opening</strong> - Small opening where urine
                  exits the body
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Vaginal opening</strong> - Entrance to the vagina
                </li>
              </ul>
            </ul>

            <h6 class="mt-3">Internal Anatomy</h6>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Vagina</strong> - Elastic, muscular canal that connects
                external genitals to the cervix
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Cervix</strong> - Lower portion of the uterus that opens
                into the vagina
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Uterus</strong> - Hollow, pear-shaped organ where a
                fertilized egg implants and fetal development occurs
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Fallopian tubes</strong> - Tubes that carry eggs from
                the ovaries to the uterus
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Ovaries</strong> - Two almond-shaped glands that produce
                eggs and hormones (estrogen and progesterone)
              </li>
            </ul>

