                  Changes in Libido
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseLibido"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingLibido"
                data-bs-parent="#sexualHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Fluctuations in sex drive are normal and can be influenced
                    by many factors:
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Hormonal changes (menstrual cycle, pregnancy, menopause)
                    </li>
                    <li>Stress, fatigue, and psychological wellbeing</li>
                    <li>Relationship factors</li>
                    <li>
                      Medications (including hormonal contraceptives and
                      antidepressants)
                    </li>
                    <li>Health conditions</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    If changes in libido cause distress, speaking with a
                    healthcare provider can help identify causes and solutions.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPain">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapsePain"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapsePain"
                >
                  Pain During Sex
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapsePain"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingPain"
                data-bs-parent="#sexualHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Pain during sexual activity (dyspareunia) should not be
                    ignored as it can signal an underlying issue:
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Insufficient lubrication</strong> - Can occur due
                      to hormonal changes, certain medications, or lack of
                      arousal
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Vaginismus</strong> - Involuntary tightening of
                      vaginal muscles
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Infections</strong> - Yeast infections, bacterial
                      vaginosis, or STIs
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Endometriosis</strong> - Tissue similar to the
                      uterine lining grows outside the uterus
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Pelvic inflammatory disease</strong> - Infection
                      of reproductive organs
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Vulvodynia</strong> - Chronic pain or discomfort
                      around the vaginal opening
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Consult with a healthcare provider to determine the cause
                    and appropriate treatment. Don't suffer in silence.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingSTIs">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseSTIs"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseSTIs"
