              <div
                id="collapseSTIs"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingSTIs"
                data-bs-parent="#sexualHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    STIs are infections spread primarily through sexual contact.
                    Many can be asymptomatic, making regular testing important.
                  </p>
                  <p><strong>Common STIs include:</strong></p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Human Papillomavirus (HPV)</li>
                    <li>Chlamydia</li>
                    <li>Gonorrhea</li>
                    <li>Herpes Simplex Virus (HSV)</li>
                    <li>Syphilis</li>
                    <li>Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV)</li>
                    <li>Trichomoniasis</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p><strong>Prevention:</strong></p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Consistent and correct use of barriers (condoms, dental
                      dams)
                    </li>
                    <li>Regular STI testing</li>
                    <li>
                      Open communication with partners about sexual health
                    </li>
                    <li>Vaccination (HPV, Hepatitis B)</li>
                    <li>Limiting number of sexual partners</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
