          <h5 class="card-title">Recommended Screenings</h5>
          <p>
            Regular screenings are essential for maintaining reproductive
            health. Here are the recommended schedules:
          </p>

          <h6 class="mt-3">Pap Smear/HPV Test</h6>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Ages 21-29:</strong> Pap test every 3 years</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Ages 30-65:</strong> Pap test and HPV test every 5 years
              (preferred) OR Pap test alone every 3 years
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>After age 65:</strong> Can stop screening if history of
              normal results
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h6 class="mt-3">STI Testing</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>All sexually active women:</strong> Annual chlamydia and
              gonorrhea screening recommended for ages 15-24
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Higher risk individuals:</strong> More frequent testing
              for STIs including HIV
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h6 class="mt-3">Breast Health</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Ages 20-39:</strong> Clinical breast exam every 1-3 years
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Ages 40+:</strong> Annual mammogram and clinical breast
              exam
            </li>
            <li><strong>All ages:</strong> Monthly breast self-awareness</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
            <p class="mb-0">
              <strong>Note:</strong> These are general guidelines. Your
              healthcare provider may recommend a different screening schedule
              based on your personal and family health history.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
